    "# GDACS Earthquake Hazard Footprint Visualization\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook demonstrates how to fetch earthquake data from the GDACS (Global Disaster Alert and Coordination System) API, process it using pystac-monty, and visualize the hazard footprints on interactive maps.\n",
    "\n",
    "We'll:\n",
    "1. Connect to the GDACS API and search for earthquake events\n",
    "2. Transform the GDACS data into STAC items\n",
    "3. Extract hazard footprints (affected areas) from the geometry data\n",
    "4. Visualize these footprints on interactive maps\n",
    "5. Analyze impact data where available\n",
    "\n",
    "Let's begin by importing the necessary libraries."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "%load_ext autoreload\n",
    "%autoreload 2\n",
    "\n",
    "# Basic libraries\n",
    "import json\n",
    "import requests\n",
    "from datetime import datetime\n",
    "\n",
    "# Visualization libraries\n",
    "import folium\n",
    "from folium.plugins import MarkerCluster\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "from IPython.display import display, HTML\n",
    "\n",
